The Telegraph - Calcutta
		 Friday, November 15, 2002 				 Ashok wins gold
																								Bangalore: Maharashtras Ashok Pandit pushed star attraction Jaspal Rana to the second spot and won the gold in the centre fire pistol event in the 46th national shooting championship on Thursday which saw two national records being shot down.																								Pandit logged 581 points, one more than Rana, who had to be content with silver, while Armys C.K. Chaudhary took the bronze (574).																								Satguru Das of Navy created a national record in the 50m rifle prone event, erasing the mark of Armys A.P. Subbaiah of 697.10 achieved in Auckland in 1999.																								Incidentally, Subbaiah picked up the silver with a tally of 693.8 and BSFs Ram Kumar finished third (691.9).																								In the centre fire pistol event in the junior national championship, Ronak Pandit improved the national record of 558 that stood in his name with an effort of 571, while Armys Manoj Kumar secured the silver (564) and his compatriot Kushal Kumar the bronze (543). (PTI)
